Commentary Text: Ashwin to Kohli, out Caught by Stoinis!! Kohli holes out to deep mid-wicket. Ashwin is a clever operator and gets rid of RCB's skipper. Out of all the DC players, Nortje will be the most relieved one out there. This was slower through the air, Virat was tempted as he came down the track to slog it out of Abu Dhabi. Got defeated by the flight and his attempted shot went up in smoke. Hits it in the air and Stoinis judges it superbly at deep mid-wicket, stepped back and completes a fine catch. Just the wicket DC wanted and Ashwin has provided them one. Kohli c Stoinis b Ashwin 29(24) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Rabada to Philippe, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw!! Rabada strikes with his first ball! Also, his first wicket in the powerplay this season. It has taken a while but he has got it in the most important game. Philippe never looked settled today and seemed scratchy. He tried to take on Delhi's best bowler first ball and perished. Good length ball not quite full enough to play the loft, the ball hits the higher part of the bat and slices over the infield on the off-side, Shaw runs back from cover-point and takes a good catch over his left shoulder. Philippe c Prithvi Shaw b Rabada 12(17) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Siraj to Prithvi Shaw, out Bowled!! What a cracker from Siraj! This is right there among the top deliveries of this IPL. Pure magic. Upright seam position, straightish line and this jags away after pitching. Shaw's feet went nowhere as he played inside the line of this one and to be fair to him, he wouldn't have expected the ball to move as much as he did. If the previous boundary he hit was just genius batting, this one from Siraj is just pure artistry from the bowler. There's the early wicket RCB were desperate for. Prithvi Shaw b Siraj 9(6) [4s-2]
